  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Drain your <strong>tofu</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Crumble the <strong>drained tofu</strong> very finely</p><p>Combine the <strong>crumbled tofu </strong>and <strong>five-spice mix </strong>in a bowl with your<strong> umami seasoning </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your<strong> soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>  – this is your <strong>umami tofu</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-dan-dan-style-tofu-udon/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>umami tofu </strong>(reserve the bowl!) to the pan and cook for 12-14 min or until golden and crispy, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go – this is your <strong>crispy tofu</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-dan-dan-style-tofu-udon/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>cornflour </strong>and<strong> remaining soy sauce </strong>in the reserved bowl<strong> </strong>with your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat go easy!), <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>,<strong> tahini </strong>and<strong> rice vinegar</strong></p><p>Add 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[85ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>– this is your<strong> dan dan-style sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-dan-dan-style-tofu-udon/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-dan-dan-style-tofu-udon/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>When the tofu is nearly ready, add your <strong>udon noodles</strong> to a bowl and cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Set aside to soak for 1-2 min, then stir to separate the noodles</p><p>Drain the <strong>soaked noodles</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-dan-dan-style-tofu-udon/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the tofu is crispy, reduce the heat to medium</p><p>Add the <strong>dan dan-style sauce </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until thickened</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-dan-dan-style-tofu-udon/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, add the <strong>drained noodles </strong>and <strong>blanched peas </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>spicy</strong> <strong>dan dan-style tofu udon</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-dan-dan-style-tofu-udon/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy dan dan-style tofu udon </strong>and top with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
